	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 2nd 3:33 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am a 28 Cleric on Xegony.  I'm finding that fighting in the dungeons that have exp bonus great right now.  Sol Eye and Splitpaw are my best friends.  Only problem comese with pulling.  Druids can't use thier haromny spell inside so I find I'm often up with the question can you calm them... I'm scared to calm it never works right and as the Cleric I don't want group members to die... so me trying to calm is bad lol.. But Lets take split paw for example.. Go in there's a red and a blue I calm the blue says he looks less agressive.. I nuke the red they both come!.. or say I nuke the blue and someone else pulls the red they still both come.. This is the same with say 3 blues I calm 2 says they look less agressive get the other all 3 come.  Why is this?  Seems like a useless spell.. It use to work :/<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
