<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99790423558662></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99790423558662><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=99790423558662>RE: How do I use the Calm Spells?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 15th 3:37 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>When you calm them, calm the one furthest away from you and then pull the one closest. I found that if an aggroed one comes to you passing the calmed one, often the calm will break and they all aggro. Just make sure you get the furthest away one to start first then come towards you.<br><br>Taushar<br>Cleric of Tunare, 33rd season<br>Xev Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
